bonusArgument.description: Agent bonus argument. Can either be a JSON string or a plain object. This bonus argument is single-use, it will only be used for the current launch. If present, it will be merged with the original argument, resulting in an effective argument that can be retrieved with buster.argument in the agent’s script.

get.description: Gets the output of the most recent container of an agent. This API endpoint is specifically designed so that it’s easy to get incremental data from an agent.

parameters.description: ID of the org that is perfoming the operation (not necessary when using a third party key)

parameters.description: Id of the agent to fetch output from.

parameters.name: fromOutputPos
parameters.description: If set, the returned output will start from the specified position.

parameters.name: prevContainerId
parameters.description: If set, the output will be retrieved from the container after the specified previous container id.

parameters.name: prevStatus
parameters.description: If set, allows to define which status was previously retrieved on user-side.

parameters.name: prevRuntimeEventIndex
parameters.description: If set, the container's runtime events will be returned in the response starting from the provided previous runtime event index.

id.description: If set, the agent with the corresponding id will be updated.

org.description: If set, the upserted agent will be linked to the specified organization.

script.description: If set, the upserted agent will be assigned to the specified script.

branch.description: If set, the upserted agent will be assigned to the specified branch.

environment.description: If set, the upserted agent will be assigned to the specified environment.
environment.title: ScriptBranchEnvironment

executionTimeLimit.description: When set, the execution time of the agent will be limited by the provided value. If this limit is exceeded, the agent will be stopped.

fileMgmtMaxFolders.description: Max amount of folders for file management.

maxParallelism.description: Sets the maximum amount of concurrent executions of the agent.

maxRetryNumber.description: Sets the maximum amount of retries the agent will do before aborting.

launchType.description: Sets how the agent will be launched. Either "manually", "repeatedly", "once" or "after agent".

launchOnceAt.description: Must be set when launchType is set to "once". Sets the launch time of the agent.

launchAfterAgentId.description: Must be set when launchType is set to "after agent". Sets the id of the agent which will trigger the launch of this agent.

repeatedLaunchTimes.description: Must be set when launchType is set to "repeatedly". Schedules when the agent will be launched automatically.

enum: Once every other working hour, excluding weekends

Thrice per working hour, excluding weekends
4 times per working hour, excluding weekends

notifications.description: Sets the notification settings of the agent.

webhook.description: Your custom webhook URL. We will post insightful informations about your agent run at this address once it's done. You might be interested in our article on [how to use webhooks](https://hub.phantombuster.com/docs/using-webhooks)

proxyType.description: If set to "none", no proxy will be used. If set to "http" a single http proxy will be used. If set to "pool" the proxies from the pool will be used.

proxyAddress.description: When "proxyType" is set to "http", this should be the http address of the proxy. When set to "pool" this should be the name of the proxy pool you wish to use.

proxyUsername.description: Sets the username used to authenticate the proxy. Should be used when "proxyType" is set to "http".

proxyPassword.description: Sets the password used to authenticate the proxy. Should be used when "proxyType" is set to "http".

argument.description: Default argument used to launch the agent.

agentObject.description: Sets the agent's object. Should be a JSON string.

repeatedLaunchPreset.description: Automatically sets the agent's launch schedule according to a preset.
enum: Once every other working hour, excluding weekends
Once per working hour, excluding weekends
Twice per working hour, excluding weekends
Thrice per working hour, excluding weekends
4 times per working hour, excluding weekends

applyScriptManifestDefaultSettings.description: If true, the manifest's default settings will be applied to the agent.

masterAgentLaunchAfter.description: Defines when the agent will launch once a slave agent finishes. When not set, the platform chooses a value between 10 and 15 minutes randomly.

masterAgentLaunchOnExitCodes.description: When set, the agent will be launched automatically if the finishing slave agent’s exit code is found in the array or if the value is set to "all".

squidLeaseIdentifier.description: Sets the agent's Squid lease configuration.
